(42, 8, 18, 41, 4, 23, 25, 'Take heed therefore how ye hear', 'Connection of Hearing and Receiving', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of how one hears and the consequences of that hearing. They share similar phrases about receiving more based on what one has or does not have.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 18, 42, 19, 26, 26, 'whosoever hath, to him shall be given', 'Connection of Stewardship and Reward', 'Both passages emphasize the principle that those who possess understanding or resources will receive more, while those lacking them will lose even what they seem to have. This highlights a consistent theme of accountability and the consequences of one''s response to what they have.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 18, 40, 25, 29, 29, 'whosoever hath, to him shall be given', 'Connection of Abundance and Lack', 'Both passages emphasize the principle that those who have will receive more, while those who lack will lose even what they seem to possess. This connection highlights a consistent theme of stewardship and the consequences of one''s response to what they have.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 18, 20, 2, 2, 5, 'take heed therefore how ye hear', 'Hearing and Seeking Wisdom', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of actively seeking understanding and wisdom. Luke 8:18 warns about how one hears, while Proverbs 2:2 encourages inclining the ear to wisdom, suggesting that the pursuit of knowledge is crucial for spiritual growth.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 18, 43, 15, 2, 2, 'whosoever hath, to him shall be given', 'Connection of Fruitfulness and Hearing', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of producing fruit or receiving understanding. The idea of being given more or having taken away reflects the necessity of being fruitful in one''s spiritual life.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 18, 58, 2, 1, 1, 'Take heed therefore how ye hear', 'Heeding What We Hear', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of how we hear and respond to teachings. Luke warns that neglecting what we have can lead to losing even that which we seem to have, while Hebrews urges earnest attention to what we have heard to prevent it from slipping away.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 19, 40, 12, 46, 50, 'his mother and his brethren', 'Family and Discipleship Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of Jesus'' mother and brethren seeking him. They highlight the distinction between biological family and those who follow God''s will, suggesting a redefinition of familial relationships in the context of discipleship.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 19, 41, 3, 21, 21, 'his mother and his brethren', 'Family Concern for Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the concern of Jesus'' family and friends regarding his behavior. In Luke, his mother and brethren come to him, while in Mark, his friends believe he is ''beside himself.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 19, 41, 3, 31, 35, 'his mother and his brethren', 'Connection of Family and Discipleship', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Jesus and his family, highlighting the distinction between biological ties and spiritual kinship. The mention of ''mother and brethren'' in both texts illustrates this theme of redefining familial bonds based on obedience to God''s will.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 20, 40, 13, 55, 56, 'thy mother and thy brethren', 'Family References in Jesus'' Life', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' familial connections, mentioning his mother and brothers. The mention of ''brethren'' in Luke aligns with the identification of Jesus'' family in Matthew, highlighting the significance of his earthly relationships.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 20, 41, 6, 3, 3, 'Thy mother and thy brethren', 'Family Recognition in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' familial relationships, highlighting the presence of his mother and brothers. This connection illustrates the tension between his earthly family and his ministry, as seen in their desire to see him and the offense taken by others at his identity.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 20, 43, 7, 3, 6, 'thy mother and thy brethren stand without', 'Family Relations and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Jesus and his brethren. In Luke, they seek to see him, while in John, they express skepticism about his works, highlighting a lack of belief.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 20, 44, 1, 14, 14, 'thy mother and thy brethren', 'Connection of Jesus'' Family', 'This connection highlights the presence of Jesus'' mother and brethren in both passages. In Luke, they desire to see Him, while in Acts, they are depicted as part of the early community of believers.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 20, 46, 9, 5, 5, 'thy mother and thy brethren', 'Connection of Jesus'' Brethren', 'This connection highlights the mention of ''brethren'' in both passages, indicating a familial relationship. Both verses emphasize the presence of Jesus'' family and the role of his brethren in the early Christian community.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 20, 48, 1, 19, 19, 'thy mother and thy brethren', 'Connection Between Jesus'' Family', 'This connection highlights the familial relationship of Jesus, as both passages mention ''brethren'' and ''brother.'' Luke 8:20 refers to Jesus'' family seeking him, while Galatians 1:19 identifies James as ''the Lordâ€™s brother,'' emphasizing the significance of Jesus'' earthly family.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 21, 42, 11, 27, 28, 'hear the word of God, and do it', 'Connection of Hearing God''s Word', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of hearing the word of God and acting upon it. In Luke 8:21, Jesus identifies his true family as those who hear and do God''s word, while in Luke 11:28, he states that those who hear and keep God''s word are blessed.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 21, 59, 1, 22, 22, 'hear the word of God, and do it', 'Connection of Hearing and Doing', 'This connection highlights the importance of not only hearing the word of God but also acting upon it. Both passages emphasize the necessity of being doers of the word, linking the concept of true kinship with God to obedience.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 21, 43, 13, 17, 17, 'do it', 'Connection of Obedience and Happiness', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of doing God''s word. Luke highlights that true kinship with Jesus is shown through action, while John states that happiness comes from doing what is known. This connection highlights the theme of obedience leading to fulfillment.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 21, 62, 2, 29, 29, NULL, 'Righteousness and Obedience Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of doing righteousness as an expression of one''s relationship with God. Both passages emphasize the importance of hearing and doing God''s word as a sign of being born of Him.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 21, 64, 1, 11, 11, NULL, 'Connection of Goodness and Obedience', 'This connection highlights the theme of doing good as a reflection of one''s relationship with God. Both passages emphasize the importance of hearing and doing the word of God as a sign of being aligned with divine goodness.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 21, 47, 6, 18, 18, 'hear the word of God, and do it', 'Connection of Divine Family', 'This connection highlights the theme of belonging to God''s family through obedience. Both passages emphasize the relationship between God and those who hear and do His word, indicating a familial bond.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 21, 58, 2, 11, 13, 'brethren are these which hear the word of God, and do it', 'Connection of Brethren Concept', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''brethren'' in relation to those who follow God''s word. Luke highlights the importance of doing God''s will to be considered part of His family, while Hebrews affirms that Jesus identifies with those He sanctifies as His brethren.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 22, 40, 8, 23, 27, 'he went into a ship with his disciples', 'Calming the Storm', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus entering a ship with his disciples, leading to a significant event on the sea. The narrative in Matthew expands on the storm and Jesus'' authority over nature, which begins with the journey initiated in Luke.', 'parallel', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 22, 41, 4, 35, 41, 'Let us go over unto the other side', 'Journey Across the Lake', 'Both passages emphasize the directive to ''pass over unto the other side,'' indicating a shared narrative moment. Additionally, they both describe the disciples'' experience during a storm, highlighting their fear and Jesus'' calming of the sea.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 22, 41, 6, 45, 45, 'Let us go over unto the other side', 'Disciples in a Ship', 'Both passages emphasize the act of the disciples getting into a ship to cross to the other side. This connection highlights the shared theme of Jesus directing his disciples in their journey across water.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 22, 40, 14, 22, 22, 'Let us go over unto the other side', 'Disciples Crossing the Lake', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus instructing his disciples to get into a ship and go to the other side. This connection highlights the shared theme of obedience and movement across water in the ministry of Jesus.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 22, 42, 5, 1, 1, 'lake', 'Journey Across the Lake', 'Both passages emphasize the lake setting, with Jesus interacting with his disciples and the crowd. The mention of the lake in both contexts highlights the significance of this geographical location in Jesus'' ministry.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 22, 42, 8, 23, 23, 'Let us go over unto the other side', 'Journey and Storm Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the journey across the lake and the ensuing storm. The transition from launching forth to facing peril highlights the challenges encountered during their voyage.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 22, 43, 6, 1, 1, 'Let us go over unto the other side', 'Journey Across the Sea', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' movement across the sea, highlighting a significant transition in his ministry. The act of going over the sea connects the two events, suggesting a continuity in Jesus'' mission.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 23, 19, 93, 3, 4, 'storm of wind on the lake', 'Storm and Divine Power', 'Both passages emphasize the power of storms and floods, highlighting the danger they pose. Luke describes a storm threatening the disciples, while Psalms proclaims the Lord''s might over the floods and waves.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
